<term-sec id="id-2ffaf68e-6af6-4aba-d348-2edd24cb7392"><tbx:termEntry xmlns:tbx="urn:iso:std:iso:30042:ed-1"><tbx:langSet xml:lang="en"><tbx:definition><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="dad72425-284a-44e7-fda1-822357f569ba" timestamp="1627810035267"?>occurrence in time that partners to a <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="dad72425-284a-44e7-fda1-822357f569ba"?><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="de15d7ce-dfa6-4f62-e811-04f4af3df40a" timestamp="1627810027009"?>learning transaction<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="de15d7ce-dfa6-4f62-e811-04f4af3df40a"?></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="93122a95-8cd8-4715-c7ce-2966b6e11ebd" timestamp="1627810027009"?> wish to monitor or control<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="93122a95-8cd8-4715-c7ce-2966b6e11ebd"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="0cbb737e-57d3-4708-9011-0e6ec9667310" text=" " timestamp="1627810027009"?></tbx:definition><tbx:note><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7a88d795-8408-413d-f552-8102646a260c" timestamp="1627810044168"?>Learning events are the workflow tasks that learning partners need to accomplish to complete a <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-e12adf88-bd24-4f73-992f-e961d98ac751.xml#id-2b6390ff-eab6-4da4-eefa-fa2c027814c7" ref-type="other" id="id-b290b841-6311-42fb-9e3e-9a8a9fa0efd7" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">learning transaction</xref> among themselves. As learning events occur, they cause a <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-e12adf88-bd24-4f73-992f-e961d98ac751.xml#id-2b6390ff-eab6-4da4-eefa-fa2c027814c7" ref-type="other" id="id-dfdc7b06-cde0-4632-cb46-eab102bcef98" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">learning transaction</xref> to move through its various phases of planning, <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-b621fa6e-c611-4377-8341-bf593d992dfd.xml#id-a10dce1e-c9d8-4023-cb8e-e704d4b13eca" ref-type="other" id="id-059d5a0d-94f4-43eb-c123-a13372cc1989" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">identification</xref>, negotiation, actualization, and post-actualization.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7a88d795-8408-413d-f552-8102646a260c"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="053d498b-129a-4ea5-a055-4979f3ae1d75" text=" " timestamp="1627810044168"?></tbx:note><tbx:note><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7942c576-5837-453b-8a9d-16d181cdec25" timestamp="1627810053043"?>Occurrences in time can either be: (1) internal as mutually agreed to among the parties to a <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-e12adf88-bd24-4f73-992f-e961d98ac751.xml#id-2b6390ff-eab6-4da4-eefa-fa2c027814c7" ref-type="other" id="id-852bd401-2406-4095-a584-60a3c111067c" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema">learning transaction</xref>; and/or, (2) reference some common publicly available and recognized date/time referencing schema, (e.g., one based on using the ISO 8601 and/or ISO 19135 standards).<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7942c576-5837-453b-8a9d-16d181cdec25"?></tbx:note><tbx:source><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="93f8da69-165b-4f41-858a-e7394d607661" timestamp="1627810068099"?>Adapted from ISO/IEC 15944-4.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="93f8da69-165b-4f41-858a-e7394d607661"?></tbx:source><tbx:tig><tbx:term><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="bcc1150d-f56a-4ca6-f561-456150cf5744" timestamp="1627810036524"?>learning event<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="bcc1150d-f56a-4ca6-f561-456150cf5744"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="73bc5ffd-f6dc-40be-a77a-50a4417bbb9e" text=" " timestamp="1627810036524"?></tbx:term><tbx:partOfSpeech value="noun"/><tbx:normativeAuthorization value="prefe